<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1748] Guard and RWGuard macros defined in global namespace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1748</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;thrift/concurrency/Mutex.h defines global macros Guard and RWGuard.  Although the purpose is well commented and appreciated - i.e. trying to prevent coders from creating temporary variables and falsely assuming they have a lock - this code does interfere with other packages that define their own Guard classes.  Even when the user/library define Guard in their own namespace, there&apos;s a clash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please remove the macros.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Visual Studio 2010&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
